<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="bacteria">Bacteria</a> - Bacteria are a <a href="#microOrganism">microorganisms</a>, classified as <a href="#prokaryote">prokaryotes</a>. They most often present themselves in a <a href="#unicellular">unicellular</a> form and always lack a <a href="#nucleus">nucleus</a>. Their <a href="#gene">genetic material</a> floats freely inside the cell and can be organised into two different sets, a <a href="#circular_prokaryote_chromosome">central circular chromosome</a> and <a href="#plasmid">plasmids</a>.